            data: {
              text: "# Risk Assessment: Climate Change Report 2025\n\n## HIGH RISKS\n\n### 1. **Accelerating Temperature Rise**\n- **Risk Level:** HIGH\n- **Issue:** 1.3\u00b0C increase approaches the 1.5\u00b0C Paris Agreement threshold\n- **Impact:** Increased frequency of extreme weather events, ecosystem disruption, agricultural stress\n- **Timeframe:** Immediate and worsening\n\n### 2. **Arctic Ice Record Low**\n- **Risk Level:** HIGH\n- **Issue:** Critical tipping point indicator; accelerates warming through reduced albedo effect\n- **Impact:** Sea level rise, disrupted ocean currents, methane release from permafrost, habitat loss\n- **Timeframe:** Cascading effects already underway\n\n### 3. **Atmospheric CO2 at 425ppm**\n- **Risk Level:** HIGH\n- **Issue:** Continues upward trajectory despite emission reductions; highest in 3+ million years\n- **Impact:** Long-term warming commitment, ocean acidification, irreversible climate changes\n- **Timeframe:** Multi-generational consequences\n\n## MODERATE RISKS\n\n### 4. **Insufficient Emission Reduction Rate**\n- **Risk Level:** MODERATE-HIGH\n- **Issue:** 2% annual decrease insufficient to meet net-zero targets (need ~7-10% annually)\n- **Impact:** Will miss climate targets, requiring more drastic future action\n- **Timeframe:** 5-10 years to course-correct\n\n## POSITIVE INDICATORS (Mitigating Factors)\n\n- Renewable energy growth (35%) shows transition momentum\n- Emissions trending downward (first step toward reversal)\n\n## CRITICAL RECOMMENDATIONS\n\n1. **Accelerate decarbonization** to 7-10% annual reductions\n2. **Deploy carbon capture** technologies at scale\n3. **Protect Arctic regions** and monitor tipping points\n4. **Enhance adaptation measures** for vulnerable populations\n\n**Overall Assessment:** System remains in critical state with inadequate response velocity.",
            },
            data_text:
              "                            Risk Assessment: Climate Change Report 2025                             \n\nHIGH RISKS                                                                                          \n\n1. Accelerating Temperature Rise                                                                    \n\n \u2022 Risk Level: HIGH                                                                                 \n \u2022 Issue: 1.3\u00b0C increase approaches the 1.5\u00b0C Paris Agreement threshold                             \n \u2022 Impact: Increased frequency of extreme weather events, ecosystem disruption, agricultural stress \n \u2022 Timeframe: Immediate and worsening                                                               \n\n2. Arctic Ice Record Low                                                                            \n\n \u2022 Risk Level: HIGH                                                                                 \n \u2022 Issue: Critical tipping point indicator; accelerates warming through reduced albedo effect       \n \u2022 Impact: Sea level rise, disrupted ocean currents, methane release from permafrost, habitat loss  \n \u2022 Timeframe: Cascading effects already underway                                                    \n\n3. Atmospheric CO2 at 425ppm                                                                        \n\n \u2022 Risk Level: HIGH                                                                                 \n \u2022 Issue: Continues upward trajectory despite emission reductions; highest in 3+ million years      \n \u2022 Impact: Long-term warming commitment, ocean acidification, irreversible climate changes          \n \u2022 Timeframe: Multi-generational consequences                                                       \n\nMODERATE RISKS                                                                                      \n\n4. Insufficient Emission Reduction Rate                                                             \n\n \u2022 Risk Level: MODERATE-HIGH                                                                        \n \u2022 Issue: 2% annual decrease insufficient to meet net-zero targets (need ~7-10% annually)           \n \u2022 Impact: Will miss climate targets, requiring more drastic future action                          \n \u2022 Timeframe: 5-10 years to course-correct                                                          \n\nPOSITIVE INDICATORS (Mitigating Factors)                                                            \n\n \u2022 Renewable energy growth (35%) shows transition momentum                                          \n \u2022 Emissions trending downward (first step toward reversal)                                         \n\nCRITICAL RECOMMENDATIONS                                                                            \n\n 1 Accelerate decarbonization to 7-10% annual reductions                                            \n 2 Deploy carbon capture technologies at scale                                                      \n 3 Protect Arctic regions and monitor tipping points                                                \n 4 Enhance adaptation measures for vulnerable populations                                           \n\nOverall Assessment: System remains in critical state with inadequate response velocity.             \n",
            data_html:
              "# Risk Assessment: Climate Change Report 2025\n\n## HIGH RISKS\n\n### 1. **Accelerating Temperature Rise**\n- **Risk Level:** HIGH\n- **Issue:** 1.3\u00b0C increase approaches the 1.5\u00b0C Paris Agreement threshold\n- **Impact:** Increased frequency of extreme weather events, ecosystem disruption, agricultural stress\n- **Timeframe:** Immediate and worsening\n\n### 2. **Arctic Ice Record Low**\n- **Risk Level:** HIGH\n- **Issue:** Critical tipping point indicator; accelerates warming through reduced albedo effect\n- **Impact:** Sea level rise, disrupted ocean currents, methane release from permafrost, habitat loss\n- **Timeframe:** Cascading effects already underway\n\n### 3. **Atmospheric CO2 at 425ppm**\n- **Risk Level:** HIGH\n- **Issue:** Continues upward trajectory despite emission reductions; highest in 3+ million years\n- **Impact:** Long-term warming commitment, ocean acidification, irreversible climate changes\n- **Timeframe:** Multi-generational consequences\n\n## MODERATE RISKS\n\n### 4. **Insufficient Emission Reduction Rate**\n- **Risk Level:** MODERATE-HIGH\n- **Issue:** 2% annual decrease insufficient to meet net-zero targets (need ~7-10% annually)\n- **Impact:** Will miss climate targets, requiring more drastic future action\n- **Timeframe:** 5-10 years to course-correct\n\n## POSITIVE INDICATORS (Mitigating Factors)\n\n- Renewable energy growth (35%) shows transition momentum\n- Emissions trending downward (first step toward reversal)\n\n## CRITICAL RECOMMENDATIONS\n\n1. **Accelerate decarbonization** to 7-10% annual reductions\n2. **Deploy carbon capture** technologies at scale\n3. **Protect Arctic regions** and monitor tipping points\n4. **Enhance adaptation measures** for vulnerable populations\n\n**Overall Assessment:** System remains in critical state with inadequate response velocity.",
